reviews.text: Very quiet place. You have 2 platforms. NO STAFF AT ALL at the station. Place to park cycles. Not. Much shelter to stand if it rains. Tickets through a machine. We get direct trains to reading. Well maintained station with respect to cleanliness and we get announcements on time but at times announcements are not very clear

Absolutely isolated. No station office, no guard, no staff, no toilet facility. 

During off peak hours the trains are only very hour. I arrived 40 mins early and was feeling unwell. 

It was a nightmare trying to get any help. Even if someone collapses on the platform, no one will notice. 

The railway authority or the council should take steps to provide basic facilities. 

Difficult to believe such stations exist not too far from London.
Not safe train station,some body took my bike even station has CCTV camers. Ticketing system is okay.
This is a train station? I thought it was a ghost town over there

Kerb outside the ticket office is odd and needs to be marked - white paint or yellow/black marking.  I've tripped up it several times and fell last night (arriving from across the line). Should say, my eyesight isn't great.
